connection.connect.pool.accessToUnderlyi: Controls whether the PoolGuard allows access to the base connections。
connection.connect.pool.defaultAutoCommi: The default auto-commit status for the connection created by the pool。
connection.connect.pool.defaultCatalog: The default directory for the connection created by the pool。
connection.connect.pool.defaultReadOnly: The default read-only status of the connection created by the pool.If it is not set, the setReadOnly method is not called。
connection.connect.pool.defaultTransacti: The connection created by the pool is in the default TransactionIsolation status。
connection.connect.pool.initialSize: The number of initial connections created when the pool is started。
connection.connect.pool.LogAbandoned: Mark to record the stack trace of the application code that has dropped the statement or connection.Since stack traces must be generated, recording the abandoned statements and connections increases the overhead of each open connection or new statement。
connection.connect.pool.maxActive: The maximum number of active connections that can be allocated from the pool simultaneously or is non-positive。
connection.connect.pool.maxIdle: The maximum number of connections left idle in the pool, no additional connections being published, or no negative limit。
connection.connect.pool.maxOpenPreparedS: The maximum number of open statements can be allocated from the statement pool simultaneously or with zero。
connection.connect.pool.maxWait: The pool waits for the maximum number of milliseconds for the connection recovery (when no connection is available) before the exception is thrown, or waits indefinitely with-1。
connection.connect.pool.minIdle: The minimum number of connections left idle in the pool, no additional connections are being published, or zero means that no connections are created。
connection.connect.pool.poolPreparedStat: Enables the statement pool prepared for this pool。
connection.connect.pool.removeAbandoned: If the abandoned connections exceed removeAbandonedTimout, then marked to remove them.If set to true, the connection is deemed abandoned and can be removed when its free time exceeds removeAbandonedTimeout.Setting it to true restores the database connection from a poorly programmed application that failed to close the connection。
connection.connect.pool.removeAbandonedT: Timeout seconds that the abandoned connection passes before it can be removed。
connection.connect.pool.testOnBorrow: Indicates whether to validate the objects before borrowing them from the pool.If the object cannot be validated, it is removed from the pool and try to borrow another object.Note-That the validationQuery parameter must be set to a non-null value string。
connection.connect.pool.testOnReturn: Indicates whether the objects are validated before being returned to the pool.Note- -the validationQuery parameter must be set to a non-null value string。
connection.connect.pool.testWhileIdle: Indicates whether the object is validated by an idle object exporter (if any).If the object cannot be verified, remove it from the pool.Note-That the validationQuery parameter must be set to a non-null value string。
connection.connect.pool.timeBetweenEvict: Number of milliseconds dormant between runs of the idle exexthread.When it is non-positive, the idle object exporter will not run。
connection.connect.pool.validationQuery: The SQL statements used to validate these connections from the pool before returning them to the caller.If specified, this query must be a SQL SELECT statement that returns at least one row。
